<h1>Alex Strick van Linschoten</h1>

<h2><a href="/">/now</a>: <a href="http://www.alexstrick.com/now">alexstrick.com/now</a></h2>

<h2>Location:</h2>
<p>
Berlin

Germany
</p>

<h2>Professional title:</h2>
<p>
Writer/researcher
</p>

<h2>What do you do?</h2>
<p>
I've written some books based on work done while living in Afghanistan, but I'm also interested in health, technology and the environment.
</p>

<h2>Why?</h2>
<p>
My curiosity is what moves me in one direction or another. It's why I ended up in Afghanistan, why I read a lot, and so on.
</p>

<h2>Recent thought or epiphany?</h2>
<p>
There is so much that can be stripped away from a life and that life still be rich and full of pleasure and soul. I'm slowly trying to find those things that I can strip away.
</p>

<h2>What should we read?</h2>
<p>
Jim Benson - “Why Limit W.I.P.” + Rohini Mohan - “Seasons of Trouble” + Karen Joy Fowler - “We Are All Completely Beside Ourselves.”
</p>

